# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example crontab for tarxiv database backups.
#
# Install with:  crontab -e   (paste below)   or   crontab scripts/backup.crontab.example
# Inspect with:  crontab -l
#
# This runs ON the server that hosts the Docker stack, so both scripts talk to
# a LOCAL Docker engine / Couchbase — no SSH or remote hosts involved. The two
# scripts handle their own GFS rotation, so cron just fires them once a day.
#
# To keep an off-site copy, run a separate rsync job on your OTHER box that
# pulls $TARXIV_BACKUP_DIR / $TARXIV_COUCHBASE_BACKUP_DIR from here (see the
# note at the bottom).
#
# Cron runs with a bare environment (no login shell), so we set PATH and the
# paths explicitly here. Adjust them to your server.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

SHELL=/bin/bash
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
# Email any stderr/cron output here (needs a working MTA); leave blank to disable.
MAILTO=""

# Absolute path to your checkout of the repo on the server.
TARXIV_REPO=/opt/tarxiv

# Where the dumps are written. Defaults live under the repo's .data dir, but a
# dedicated location is easier for the rsync job on the other box to target.
TARXIV_BACKUP_DIR=/srv/backups/tarxiv/postgres
TARXIV_COUCHBASE_BACKUP_DIR=/srv/backups/tarxiv/couchbase

# Optional: override the GFS retention windows (defaults shown).
# TARXIV_KEEP_DAILY_DAYS=7
# TARXIV_KEEP_WEEKLY_DAYS=90
# TARXIV_KEEP_MONTHLY_DAYS=365

#   min  hour  dom  mon  dow   command
# Postgres dump every day at 02:30.
30   2    *    *    *    cd $TARXIV_REPO && ./scripts/backup_postgres.sh >> /var/log/tarxiv/pg-backup.log 2>&1

# Couchbase dump (both scopes) every day at 03:00.
0    3    *    *    *    cd $TARXIV_REPO && uv run python scripts/db_utils.py --backup >> /var/log/tarxiv/couchbase-backup.log 2>&1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Notes
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# * mkdir -p /var/log/tarxiv  (and chown it to the cron user) first, or the
#   redirects above will fail silently.
# * `uv` must be on PATH for the cron user. If it lives in ~/.local/bin or
#   ~/.cargo/bin, add that dir to PATH above, or call it by absolute path.
# * The postgres script auto-loads setup/.env for credentials and talks to the
#   local compose `postgres` service. db_utils.py connects via TarxivDB using
#   the usual local Couchbase config (TARXIV_COUCHBASE_HOST etc.), so make sure
#   that resolves for the cron user — typically localhost when run on the host.
# * Off-site copy: on your other box, a pull-based rsync keeps a remote copy,
#   e.g. a cron line there like:
#       15 4 * * * rsync -az --delete \
#         server.internal:/srv/backups/tarxiv/ /srv/backups/tarxiv-mirror/
#   Schedule it after these jobs finish (here 04:15, comfortably after 03:00).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
